title: Apple, Facebook's Frosty Relations Have Origins In Cook Confronting Zuckerberg Over Data Privacy Back In 2019: NYT
text: Apple Inc (NASDAQ: AAPL) CEO Tim Cook warned his Facebook Inc (NASDAQ: FB) counterpart to delete third-party data about users in 2019, The New York Times reported Monday. What Happened: The conversation between the two tech leaders reportedly took place at the Sun Valley gathering in Idaho at a time when Zuckerberg was grappling with the Cambridge Analytica Scandal, which involved a data compromise involving 50 million users of the social network.
